    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Vandal Lock</title>
        <para>The vandal lock option is located forward of the side entry door below the passenger side windshield wing
            panel. To remove the vandal lock assembly the passenger side of the dash panel must be removed.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Beginning at the passenger side wing panel glass, locate the mounting screw and tab for the
                passenger entry dash panel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mounting screws on the forward, leading edge of the dash panel assembly.</para>
            <figure id="f47003108" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003108.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003108.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 108. Dash Panel Remove to Access Vandal Lock</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CURB SIDE WING PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CURB SIDE PANEL COVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the mounting screws along the bottom edge of the dash panel and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the dash panel up and out of the way.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the vandal lock assembly on the interior panel forward of the passenger entry and
                over the cross bus beam.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wire connections to the vandal lock assembly.</para>
            <figure id="f47003109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003109.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003109.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 109. Disconnect Wire Connections- Vandal Lock</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VANDAL LOCK HARNESS CONNECTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VANDAL LOCK INTERIOR JAM NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CROSS BEAM SUPPORT MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">CROSS BUS BEAM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the vandal lock interior surface lock jam nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the exterior trim ring on vandal lock key shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the lock ring on the outside body panel section of the vehicle, remove the nut and
                washer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the vandal lock assembly out of the mounting hole from inside.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
